name: Air Elemental
text: Flying
flavor: As insubstantial, and as powerful, as the wind that carries it.

name: Blizzard Elemental
text: Flying\n{3}{U}: Untap Blizzard Elemental.
flavor: Students who had seen Rayne argue with Urza were certain she had summoned it to make him seem warmer by comparison.

name: Brainstorm
text: Draw three cards, then put two cards from your hand on top of your library in any order.
flavor: "I reeled from the blow, and then suddenly, I knew exactly what to do. Within moments victory was mine."\n—Gustha Ebbasdotter\nKjeldoran royal mage

name: Cloud Djinn
text: Flying\nCloud Djinn can block only creatures with flying.
flavor: As elusive as the footprint of a djinn\n—Suq'Ata expression

name: Cloud Elemental
text: Flying\nCloud Elemental can block only creatures with flying.
flavor: "You know you've angered the gods when the clouds turn against you."\n—Sisay, Captain of the Weatherlight

name: Counterspell
text: Counter target spell.

name: Fog Elemental
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhen Fog Elemental attacks or blocks, sacrifice it at end of combat.
flavor: "I've seen fog so thick you could cut it, but none that could cut me."\n—Tahngarth of the Weatherlight

name: Gaseous Form
text: Enchant creature\nPrevent all combat damage that would be dealt to and dealt by enchanted creature.
flavor: "It's hard to hurt anyone when you're as transparent as your motives."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Giant Crab
text: {U}: Giant Crab gains shroud until end of turn. (It can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
flavor: During the giant crabs' mating season, Skyshroud nights are filled with the clatter of their skirmishes.

name: Impulse
text: Look at the top four cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.
flavor: "Controlling time ensures you need never look impulsive again."\n—Teferi

name: Killer Whale
text: {U}: Killer Whale gains flying until end of turn.
flavor: Hunger is like the sea: deep, endless, and unforgiving.

name: Leviathan
text:
Trample
Leviathan enters the battlefield tapped and doesn't untap during your untap step.
At the beginning of your upkeep, you may sacrifice two Islands. If you do, untap Leviathan.
Leviathan can't attack unless you sacrifice two Islands. (This cost is paid as attackers are declared.)

name: Mahamoti Djinn
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: Of royal blood among the spirits of the air, the Mahamoti djinn rides on the wings of the winds. As dangerous in the gambling hall as he is in battle, he is a master of trickery and misdirection.

name: Power Sink
text: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {X}. If he or she doesn't, that player taps all lands with mana abilities he or she controls and empties his or her mana pool.

name: Snapping Drake
text: Flying
flavor: Drakes claim to be dragons—until the dragons show up.

name: Tolarian Winds
text: Discard all the cards in your hand, then draw that many cards.
flavor: Afterward, Tolaria's winds were like the whispers of lost wizards, calling for life.

name: Vigilant Drake
text: Flying\n{2}{U}: Untap Vigilant Drake.
flavor: Awake and awing in the blink of an eye.

name: Wayward Soul
text: Flying\n{U}: Put Wayward Soul on top of its owner's library.
flavor: "no home    no heart    no hope"\n—Stronghold graffito

name: Bone Harvest
text: Put any number of target creature cards from your graveyard on top of your library.\nDraw a card at the beginning of the next turn's upkeep.
flavor: "Only fools believe they will face my armies but once."\n—Kaervek

name: Coercion
text: Target opponent reveals his or her hand. You choose a card from it. That player discards that card.
flavor: "There's very little that escapes me, Greven. And you will escape very little if you fail."\n—Volrath

name: Dark Ritual
text: Add {B}{B}{B} to your mana pool.

name: Death Stroke
text: Destroy target tapped creature.
flavor: For a sharp second, Selenia froze, and Crovax's blade found home, As the angel shattered like glass, Crovax felt his mind collapse—the curse had been fulfilled.

name: Diabolic Edict
text: Target player sacrifices a creature.
flavor: Greven il-Vec lifted Vhati off his feet. "The fall will give you time to think on your failure."

name: Drain Life
text: Spend only black mana on X.\nDrain Life deals X damage to target creature or player. You gain life equal to the damage dealt, but not more life than the player's life total before Drain Life dealt damage or the creature's toughness.

name: Fallen Angel
text: Flying\nSacrifice a creature: Fallen Angel gets +2/+1 until end of turn.
flavor: "Angels are simply extensions of truth upon the fabric of life—and there is far more dark than light." —Baron Sengir

name: Feral Shadow
text: Flying
flavor: "The nightstalkers are such a minor power in Urborg. Their sad eagerness to elevate themselves makes them willing tools in the plundering of little Femeref."\n—Kaervek

name: Gravedigger
text: When Gravedigger enters the battlefield, you may return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: A full coffin is like a full coffer—both are attractive to thieves.

name: Hollow Dogs
text: Whenever Hollow Dogs attacks, it gets +2/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: A hollow dog is never empty. It is filled with thirst for the hunt.

name: Sengir Vampire
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhenever a creature dealt damage by Sengir Vampire this turn dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Sengir Vampire.

name: Skittering Horror
text: When you cast a creature spell, sacrifice Skittering Horror.
flavor: "This monstrosity will do—for now."\n—Davvol, Evincar of Rath

name: Skittering Skirge
text: Flying\nWhen you cast a creature spell, sacrifice Skittering Skirge.
flavor: The imps' warbling cries echo through Phyrexia's towers like those of mourning doves in a cathedral.

name: Tar Pit Warrior
text: When Tar Pit Warrior becomes the target of a spell or ability, sacrifice it.
flavor: "The cyclops shrugged off savage blows, but casual insults made him weep."\n—Azeworai, "The Cyclops who Couldn't"

name: Terror
text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Balduvian Horde
text: When Balduvian Horde enters the battlefield, sacrifice it unless you discard a card at random.

name: Ball Lightning
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)\nHaste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\nAt the beginning of the end step, sacrifice Ball Lightning.

name: Bloodrock Cyclops
text: Bloodrock Cyclops attacks each turn if able.
flavor: "He's big an' dumb an' ready to fight. A lot like ol' Hornhead here."\n—Squee, goblin cabin hand,\nscouting report

name: Fireball
text: Fireball deals X damage divided evenly, rounded down, among any number of target creatures and/or players.\nFireball costs {1} more to cast for each target beyond the first.

name: Hulking Cyclops
text: Hulking Cyclops can't block.
flavor: Anyone can get around a cyclops, but few can stand in its way.

name: Kird Ape
text: Kird Ape gets +1/+2 as long as you control a Forest.

name: Lava Axe
text: Lava Axe deals 5 damage to target player.
flavor: "Catch!"

name: Lightning Bolt
text: Lightning Bolt deals 3 damage to target creature or player.

name: Lowland Giant
flavor: "Faugh!" snorted Tahngarth. "Why would it make a meal of something like you?" Squee looked relieved. "No," he continued, "you'd make a much better toothpick."

name: Raging Goblin
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: He raged at the world, at his family, at his life. But mostly he just raged.

name: Shivan Dragon
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{R}: Shivan Dragon gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: While it's true most dragons are cruel, the Shivan dragon seems to take particular glee in the misery of others, often tormenting its victims much like a cat plays with a mouse before delivering the final blow.

name: Shock
text: Shock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Lightning tethers souls to the world.\n—Kor saying

name: Sonic Burst
text: As an additional cost to cast Sonic Burst, discard a card at random.\nSonic Burst deals 4 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: Music scythes the savage beast.

name: Talruum Minotaur
text: Haste
flavor: Don't insult a Talruum unless your mount is swift.\n—Suq'Ata saying

name: Thunderbolt
text: Choose one —\n• Thunderbolt deals 3 damage to target player.\n• Thunderbolt deals 4 damage to target creature with flying.
flavor: "Most wizards consider a thunderbolt to be a proper retort."\n—Ertai, wizard adept

name: Thundering Giant
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: The giant was felt a few seconds before he was seen.

name: Viashino Warrior
flavor: "When traveling the Great Desert avoid wearing the scales of lizards, for the Viashino rule the sands and look poorly on the skinning of their cousins."\n—Zhalfirin Guide to the Desert

name: Crash of Rhinos
text: Trample
flavor: Love is like a rhino, short-sighted and hasty; if it cannot find a way, it will make a way.\n—Femeref adage

name: Crashing Boars
text: Whenever Crashing Boars attacks, defending player chooses an untapped creature he or she controls. That creature blocks Crashing Boars this turn if able.
flavor: Bores ruin a party. Boars are party to ruin.

name: Deadly Insect
text: Shroud (This creature can't be the target of spells or abilities.)
flavor: With his newfound sense of self-importance, Squee set his sights on ever-bigger bugs.

name: Erhnam Djinn
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, target non-Wall creature an opponent controls gains forestwalk until your next upkeep. (It can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)

name: Fog
text: Prevent all combat damage that would be dealt this turn.

name: Force of Nature
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, Force of Nature deals 8 damage to you unless you pay {G}{G}{G}{G}.

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Llanowar Elves
text: {T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.
flavor: One bone broken for every twig snapped underfoot.\n—Llanowar penalty for trespassing

name: Plated Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: Most spiders wait patiently for their prey to arrive. Most spiders aren't forty feet tall.

name: Quirion Elves
text: As Quirion Elves enters the battlefield, choose a color.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\n{T}: Add one mana of the chosen color to your mana pool.

name: Rampant Growth
text: Search your library for a basic land card and put that card onto the battlefield tapped. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: Rath forces plants from its surface as one presses whey from cheese.

name: Scaled Wurm
flavor: "Flourishing during the Ice Age, these wurms were the bane of all Kjeldorans. Their great size and ferocity made them the subject of countless nightmares—they embodied the worst of the Ice Age."\n—Kjeldor: Ice Civilization

name: Shambling Strider
text: {R}{G}: Shambling Strider gets +1/-1 until end of turn.
flavor: Freyalise forbid that any stranger should wander into the striders' territory.

name: Wild Growth
text: Enchant land\nWhenever enchanted land is tapped for mana, its controller adds {G} to his or her mana pool (in addition to the mana the land produces).

name: Woolly Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)\nWhenever Woolly Spider blocks a creature with flying, Woolly Spider gets +0/+2 until end of turn.
flavor: "We need not fear the forces of the air; I've yet to see a spider without an appetite."\n—Taaveti of Kelsinko, elvish hunter

name: Yavimaya Wurm
text: Trample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)
flavor: When the gorilla playfully grabbed the wurm's tail, the wurm doubled back and playfully ate the gorilla's head.

name: Diabolic Vision
text: Look at the top five cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on top of your library in any order.
flavor: "I have seen the true path. I will not warm myself by the fire—I will become the flame."\n—Lim-Dûl, the Necromancer

name: Segmented Wurm
text: Whenever Segmented Wurm becomes the target of a spell or ability, put a -1/-1 counter on it.
flavor: "If only we could so easily leave behind those parts of ourselves that pain us."\n—Crovax

name: Clockwork Avian
text:
Flying
Clockwork Avian enters the battlefield with four +1/+0 counters on it.
At end of combat, if Clockwork Avian attacked or blocked this combat, remove a +1/+0 counter from it.
{X}, {T}: Put up to X +1/+0 counters on Clockwork Avian. This ability can't cause the total number of +1/+0 counters on Clockwork Avian to be greater than four. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.

name: Clockwork Beast
text: Clockwork Beast enters the battlefield with seven +1/+0 counters on it.\nAt end of combat, if Clockwork Beast attacked or blocked this combat, remove a +1/+0 counter from it.\n{X}, {T}: Put up to X +1/+0 counters on Clockwork Beast. This ability can't cause the total number of +1/+0 counters on Clockwork Beast to be greater than seven. Activate this ability only during your upkeep.

name: Dwarven Ruins
text: Dwarven Ruins enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {R} to your mana pool.\n{T}, Sacrifice Dwarven Ruins: Add {R}{R} to your mana pool.

name: Ebon Stronghold
text: Ebon Stronghold enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.\n{T}, Sacrifice Ebon Stronghold: Add {B}{B} to your mana pool.

name: Havenwood Battleground
text: Havenwood Battleground enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\n{T}, Sacrifice Havenwood Battleground: Add {G}{G} to your mana pool.

name: Polluted Mire
text: Polluted Mire enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {B} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Remote Isle
text: Remote Isle enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {U} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Slippery Karst
text: Slippery Karst enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {G} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Smoldering Crater
text: Smoldering Crater enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {R} to your mana pool.\nCycling {2} ({2}, Discard this card: Draw a card.)

name: Svyelunite Temple
text: Svyelunite Temple enters the battlefield tapped.\n{T}: Add {U} to your mana pool.\n{T}, Sacrifice Svyelunite Temple: Add {U}{U} to your mana pool.
